The paper discusses the evaluation of citation-based metrics for research evaluation purposes, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on network-based metrics and their ability to identify milestone papers and patents in large citation datasets. This topic is relevant to the sub-categories of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and social and economic systems (cs.SOC). Therefore, these are the five most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
